+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01NvEZmguKs7rqQTeejtNS46","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me analyze all the bugs using the pivot approach — looking at the system holistically:\n\n**Bug 1: `OrderRepository.update` doesn't merge with existing data** (line 38 of `repository.ts`)\n- `const updated = { ...updates, id, updatedAt: Date.now() } as Order;` — this replaces the entire order with just the updates, losing all other fields.\n- Fix: merge with `existing` first: `{ ...existing, ...updates, id, updatedAt: Date.now() }`\n\n**Bug 2: `EventBus` uses global handlers** (line 4 of `bus.ts`)\n- `globalHandlers` is module-level, shared across all `EventBus` instances. Tests create new instances in `beforeEach` but handlers accumulate.\n- Fix: Move handlers to instance level.\n\n**Bug 3: `BillingService.handleRefund` not bound to `this`** (line 25 of `service.ts`)\n- `this.eventBus.on(ORDER_EVENTS.REFUNDED, this.handleRefund);` — missing `.bind(this)`\n- Fix: Add `.bind(this)`\n\n**Bug 4: `calculateOrderTotal` doesn't round the final total** (line 23 of `calculator.ts`)\n- `const total = afterDiscount + taxAmount;` — no rounding applied\n- Fix: `Math.round(total * 100) / 100`\n\n**Bug 5: `InventoryService.handleOrderCancelled` checks `status !== 'cancelled'`** (line 50 of `service.ts`)\n- The cancellation event emitted by `OrderService` doesn't include a `status` field. The check `if (eventWithItems.status !== 'cancelled') return;` will cause the handler to return early since `status` is undefined.\n- Looking at the test: it sends `status: 'cancelled'` directly. But when called from `OrderService.cancelOrder`, the event doesn't include `status`.\n- Wait, the inventory test sends `status: 'cancelled'` explicitly. But the `OrderService.cancelOrder` emits without `status`. So the problem is the event emitted from `OrderService` doesn't include `status`.\n- Actually the test at line 73-79 of inventory.test.ts sends `status: 'cancelled'`, so the handler needs that.\n- The real problem: the inventory test at line 63-83 works directly with the event bus. But inventory tests fail at lines 66 and 87 on `order.created`. The `CREATED` handler runs and tries to reserve, but since `globalHandlers` is shared, handlers from *previous test runs* might be lingering. That's Bug 2 (global handlers).\n\n**Bug 6: `refundOrder` uses `>=` instead of `>` for the 30-day check** (line 99 of `service.ts`)\n- The test \"allows refund on exactly day 30\" expects refund to succeed at exactly 30 days\n- `if (daysSinceCreation >= REFUND_WINDOW_DAYS)` rejects at day 30\n- Fix: Change to `>` (day 30 is within the window, day 31 is not)\n\nNow let me apply all fixes."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6655,"cache_read_input_tokens":29545,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6655},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1cb4d269-3714-4b96-9f7b-4bbc0ad39ee2","uuid":"9b423d2d-942f-4e6e-b5e7-9bb4637b45c0"}
